==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kayak
<hw>Kay"ak</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
light canoe, made of skins stretched over a frame, and usually capable
of carrying but one person, who sits amidships and uses a double-bladed
paddle. It is peculiar to the Eskimos and other Arctic tribes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kayaker</ent>⟦br⟧
